        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 10 at 7:55PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 754 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles west of Downtown Concord, or near West Concord, moving east at
20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Downtown Concord, West Concord, Charlotte Motor Speedway, Harrisburg,
and Northeast Charlotte.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
